<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-492-503  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 492 503.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  Oct 1 1990 v4 n35 p35(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DOD standard ADP systems to be ready by early 1991. (theDepartment of Defense Corporate Information Management program)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brewin, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US Department of Defense's (DOD's) Corporate InformationManagement (CIM) program office expects to complete development ofstandard ADP systems for DOD-wide civilian payroll systems anddistribution centers by Feb or Mar 1991.andP;  Other functional areaspending standard information systems include materials management,personnel, financial operations, contract payment andgovernment-furnished property.andP;  The CIM office began developingADP systems in response to the 1989 Defense Management Reviewordered by President Bush and Defense Secretary Dick Cheney.andP;  Thecivilian payroll and distribution center systems, which will becompleted first, will serve as guides for other functional systemgroups.andP;  Only after standards have been established may individualservices expect to get approval for new service-specific ADPsystems.andP;  Both Army and Navy ADP systems are in progress.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Department of DefenseManagement of EDPMilitaryOffice AutomationStandardsGovernment ContractsInformation SystemsGovernment Agency.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>